  "text": "We distinguish between static and dynamic DVS. Static techniques use off-line parameters, such as periods (or minimum interarrival times) and worst-case execution cycles (WCECs), to select the appropriate voltage/speed operating mode to be used. Dynamic techniques (based on slack reclamation) take advantage of early completions of tasks to further reduce the speed and save more energy [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
